      'Every square is a unit of responsibility. You start with one. Ownership is not a byproduct of seniority — it\'s a practice. Own one square completely and you understand what you\'re scaling.',
  },
  {
    icon: '&#128172;',
    title: 'The Conference Room',
    description:
      'You cannot explain something clearly if you don\'t understand it. The conference room method — explain it until you can\'t, then go deeper — is the most effective learning tool most organizations have abandoned.',
  },
  {
    icon: '&#9651;',
    title: 'Bounded vs. Unbounded',
    description:
      'Most junior engineers have only ever operated in bounded space. This curriculum makes the distinction explicit and teaches you to recognize which type of problem you\'re in — because the tools are completely different.',
  },
  {
    icon: '&#127914;',
    title: 'Four Hats',
    description:
      'PM, Marketer, Sales Lead, CTO. Each is a lens on the same problem. Owning a square fully means seeing it through each lens — knowing when to go deep, when familiarity is enough, and when to bring in a domain expert.',
